<DOC><DOCNO> AP880526-0051 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-26-88 0440EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r a PM-ConvictsEscape     05-26 0194</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Convicts Escape,170</SECOND><HEAD>Convicted Murderer, Drug Dealer Escape From Youth Center</HEAD><DATELINE>LAUREL, Md. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Two teen-agers _ one convicted of murder andthe other of dealing cocaine _ escaped from a youth detentioncenter outside the nation's capital, but the drug dealer wasrecaptured a short time later, officials said.   District of Columbia Human Services spokeswoman Rae Parr-Mooresaid the two 17 year olds may have had outside help in their escapeWednesday, since the fence at the Oak Hill youth center justoutside the District had been cut open from the outside.   Oak Hill houses 155 juvenile felons from the District ofColumbia.   Parr-Moore said the teens had been on their way to a trainingexercise when they escaped through a two-foot hole in the fence.They were discovered missing at about 9 a.m. EDT, Parr-Moore said.   U.S. Park Police said Rashawan Gatlin was arrested laterWednesday, but the other escapee, Fernando Smith, remained at large.   Park Police Sergeant Karl Ore said the teens had been spotted inan allegedly stolen car at early afternoon on theBaltimore-Washington parkway, but that one ``bailed out of thecar'' to avoid being recaptured.</TEXT></DOC>